theorem Topology.interior_union_closure_frontier_eq_closure
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    interior A ∪ closure (frontier A) = closure A := by
  -- Show the left‐hand side is contained in `closure A`.
  apply Set.Subset.antisymm
  · intro x hx
    cases hx with
    | inl hInt =>
        -- `interior A ⊆ closure A`
        exact (interior_subset : interior A ⊆ closure A) hInt
    | inr hClosFront =>
        -- `closure (frontier A) ⊆ closure A`
        have hSub : (frontier A : Set X) ⊆ closure A :=
          Topology.frontier_subset_closure (A := A)
        exact (closure_mono hSub) hClosFront
  · intro x hxClos
    -- Decompose `closure A` as `interior A ∪ frontier A`.
    have hDecomp := Topology.interior_union_frontier_eq_closure (A := A)
    have hxUnion : x ∈ interior A ∪ frontier A := by
      simpa [hDecomp] using hxClos
    cases hxUnion with
    | inl hInt =>
        exact Or.inl hInt
    | inr hFront =>
        -- `frontier A ⊆ closure (frontier A)`
        exact Or.inr (subset_closure hFront)
